article.headline: Ohio 91, Bellarmine 74
article.story: LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Jerome Tillman led four Ohio players in double figures with 23 points to lead the Bobcats to a 91-74 win over Bellarmine in the NABC Classic on Saturday at Freedom Hall. Stephen King scored 17 points for Ohio, Sonny Troutman added 16 and Leon Williams chipped in 10 points as the Bobcats (5-2) rebounded from a loss to Louisville thanks to some hot shooting. Ohio shot a school-record 72.7 percent from the floor (32-of-44) and never trailed. The previous school record for field goal percentage was 67.9 percent set against Stetson on Dec. 2, 1978. Adam Brames led Bellarmine (3-4) with 21 points while Matt Otte added 17 and Dzaflo Larkai had 10 for the Knights, a Division II school from Louisville. Ohio was hot from the start and never really cooled off. The Bobcats shot 81 percent from the floor in the first half, missing four shots. King made all five of his 3-point attempts in the half as the Bobcats took a 49-40 lead. Bellarmine, like it did in a loss to St. Joseph's on Friday night, hung around for most of the night. The Knights pulled within 70-65 with around eight minutes to play, but the Bobcats went on a 10-0 run to pull away.
